def cross_corr(x, y, lag):
  n = len(x)
  xs = scaler.fit_transform(x.values.reshape(-1, 1)).ravel()
  ys = scaler.fit_transform(y.values.reshape(-1, 1)).ravel()
  coefs = []
  #    
  for i in range(lag):
    coefs.append(pearsonr(ys[:n-i], xs[i:])[0])
  #    
  for i in range(lag+1):
    coefs.append(pearsonr(xs[:n-i], ys[i:])[0])
  return np.arange(-lag, lag+1), np.array(coefs)

In [489]:
def get_distances(sop):
    cross_corr_matrix = []
    for col_i in sop.columns[0:]:
        cross_corr_i = []
        for col_j in sop.columns[0:]:
            lags, crs_ij = cross_corr(sop[col_i], sop[col_j], 150)
            if crs_ij.max() >= 0.7:
                dist = lags[int(np.mean(np.where(crs_ij == crs_ij.max())[0]))]
                cross_corr_i.append(dist)
            else:
                cross_corr_i.append(0)
        cross_corr_matrix.append(cross_corr_i)
    return np.array(cross_corr_matrix)
